From 6100f62be859dd37c84541b26bcf0b1f88acc37e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Edmundson <kde@davidedmundson.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 25 Sep 2025 16:21:37 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] fakeinput: Support arbitrary keysyms

When getting a keycode that cannot map to a given keycode in the current
keymap install a temporary keymap within kwin and for all clients that
contains the current symbol. This allows us to inject any unicode symbol
from fake input regardless of the current keymap.

This commit also improves the mapping of artbitrary levels to be more
technically correct.

This will also be relevant when libei gets keysym support.
